A vintage 1970s-style illustration of a lone traveler sitting in an airplane window seat at night, bathed in the soft glow of a laptop screen displaying cascading lines of code and XML brackets. Outside the small oval window, clouds drift past a crescent moon. The cabin is dark with sleeping passengers visible as silhouettes. On the tray table, scattered items suggest a developer's toolkit: a small notebook, earbuds trailing their cord. The color palette features warm amber from the screen contrasting with deep navy blues of the nighttime cabin. The aesthetic evokes retro airline travel posters with slightly muted, grainy textures and rounded geometric shapes characteristic of the era. The composition emphasizes the cozy isolation of working offline at 35,000 feet, capturing the satisfaction of being prepared and self-sufficient while disconnected from the world below.
